description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Admin Support - Band 2 FTC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;37.5 hours to cover from 08:00am to 17:00pm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coventry and Warwickshire Partnership Trust are looking for two full time enthusiastic and self-motivated persons to join our admin team on 6 months Fixed Term Contract, based at Paybody Building, Coventry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will play an important role within the wider Admin Team to provide efficient and comprehensive administrative support to clinicians and managers . You will work within a skilled mixed Admin Team in the building to support admin and clinical services and duties will include data inputting, telephone queries, care records management and filing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for individuals with a positive approach to change who are supportive of service improvements. You must be able to build effective working relationships, be approachable and accessible with a flexible approach to work. The essential requirements of this post are good telephone manner, high level communication skills, accuracy and attention to detail. You will have good organisational skills and the ability to work both independently and as part of a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be educated to GCSE level with an administration NVQ or QCF Level 2, or equivalent experience. Excellent IT skills are essential, with experience of Word processing, Carenotes, Excel data entry and email.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please note Trust interviews are currently taking place through Microsoft Teams, this can be downloaded either through the App Store or Google Play for use on your phone/tablet. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sophie Hemmings - Admin Team Coordinator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sophie.Hemmings@covwarkpt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
